// E2E tests for Protocol define: declarations in the REPL (BT-1612)
//
// Verifies that protocol definitions work in the REPL, including
// runtime registration and type parameters.
//
// Note: extending: between protocols defined in separate REPL expressions
// requires protocol hierarchy tracking (the compiler port doesn't yet
// receive previously-defined protocols in the class hierarchy). This is
// tested via BUnit where both protocols are in the same file.

// ===========================================================================
// Basic protocol definition
// ===========================================================================

Protocol define: ReplTestable
// => Protocol ReplTestable defined

// Verify it's registered
Protocol isProtocol: #ReplTestable
// => true

// ===========================================================================
// Protocol with type parameters
// ===========================================================================

Protocol define: ReplContainer(E)
// => Protocol ReplContainer defined

Protocol isProtocol: #ReplContainer
// => true

// ===========================================================================
// Non-existent protocol returns false
// ===========================================================================

Protocol isProtocol: #ReplNonExistentProto
// => false
